      "description": "The site was a Cold War continuity-of-government bunker built into the mountain above the town. Preston seized it in the first month; his first act of governance was to reinforce its walls. A Species C artisan extended the audience hall with matter-manipulated stone that does not weather. The hall smells of cold air and machine oil. Preston rarely appears in it. Outside, the approach road is patrolled at three checkpoints. Visitors who pass the checkpoints are received at the outer barracks and processed through a series of formalities before the audience chamber. The formalities are not intimidation \u2014 they are calibration, and Whelan and Amar run them together.",
